The paper deals with action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a generative adversarial network (GAN) and a transfer learning network (CPTN), which are both commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments on three different datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural network (cs.NE) research.
